>
  <p>A No Objection Certificate (NOC) is a legal document issued by one party stating they have no objection to an action taken by another party. NOCs are required for vehicle transfers, job changes, loan closures, property transactions, and many other purposes in India. The NOC Generator on TextWonder creates a formatted NOC in seconds.</p>

  <h2>How to Generate an NOC</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <a href="https://textwonder.com/tools/noc-generator">textwonder.com/tools/noc-generator</a></li>
    <li>Select the NOC type: Employment, Vehicle, Property, Bank, College, or Custom.</li>
    <li>Fill in the required fields — they change based on the NOC type selected.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Generate NOC</strong>.</li>
    <li>Review and edit the generated NOC if needed.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Print / Save as PDF</strong> to download.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>NOC Types Explained</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Employment NOC</strong> — Issued by an employer allowing an employee to apply for other jobs or work elsewhere</li>
    <li><strong>Vehicle NOC</strong> — Issued by a bank or financier after full loan repayment for RTO transfer</li>
    <li><strong>Property NOC</strong> — Issued by a housing society or builder for sale, mortgage, or renovation</li>
    <li><strong>Bank / Loan NOC</strong> — Issued after a loan is fully repaid, certifying no outstanding dues</li>
    <li><strong>College NOC</strong> — Issued to students for internships, events, or transfers</li>
    <li><strong>Custom</strong> — Flexible template for any other NOC requirement</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Making the NOC Official</h2>
  <p>Print the NOC on your organisation's official letterhead. Have it signed by an authorised signatory (HR Manager, Principal, Branch Manager, etc.) with the official rubber stamp. Some institutions also require it to be notarised for high-value transactions.</p>

